On today's programme: Fleeing from the Taliban; how to be a 'good wife'; and running marathons at 98. With Ritula Shah. Refugees in Pakistan They fled from the battle with the Taliban - Javeria Malik from Action Aid tells Outlook how Pakistan's refugees are coping. Zambia's wife teachers The women in Zambia teaching the traditional qualities they say you need to be a good wife. The 98 year old marathon runner Running and training - the fitness and health secrets of 98 year old Fauja Singh Show less